$interpreted: Tica: Whew... Pang, you're way too fast!
Pang: We've got no time! If she's been caught by the honey badgers—
Tica: Well it's no use if we can't keep up with you, either! Juan-Yun's our ticket in, and he's way behind!
Elio: Why is Pang so worked up? Just because of the honey badgers?
Juan-Yun: I think so, and you can't blame him. I feel bad holding him back.
Elio: I don't get it... You all say the honey badgers are fierce, but the whole East Alliance is fierce. Hasn't anyone been able to deal with them?
Tindoiimu: ......
Juan-Yun: ...They're definitely not the strongest in the Alliance, in terms of pure physical strength.
Elio: Then—
Juan-Yun: —But they're fearless. They don't quit.
Juan-Yun: Their leader, Sennosuke, once wiped out an entire tribe because of some debt. Since then, everyone's been terrified of the honey badgers.
Elio: A whole tribe? And the Alliance didn't do anything about it?
Juan-Yun: The Alliance, they...
Juan-Yun: You wouldn't really understand, Elio, you're not from here.
Juan-Yun: We're an alliance in name, but in reality, everyone looks out for themselves. They only care about their own sovereignty and their own profit.
Elio: So they don't stick their noses in the honey badgers' business?
Tindoiimu: ...It's worse than that...
Elio: Worse?
Juan-Yun: The honey badgers hand out bribes, and each tribe just... looks the other way.
Juan-Yun: ...It's despicable, really.
Tindoiimu: ......
Elio: ...The wind is strong here. Getting hard to stand...
Pang: These are the Wind-Sect city walls.
Tica: Wow, I've never seen such cool city walls!
Tica: Actually, I haven't really seen any city walls, so...
Juan-Yun: Well, thank you. It's nice to get compliments from such a pretty girl. Even if this wall were to fall, it'd be worth it just to hear that.
Tica: Pretty girl? You mean, me?
Juan-Yun: Of course, Tica. You carry such a unique beauty.
Tica: Haha well, naturally, you'd be a fool not to see it.
Tindoiimu: ...They seem to be getting along.

Elio: ...Yeah, I'm surprised, too. 
She's not wrong, though—these city walls are really something.
Pang: The Alliance Hall is one of our most important buildings, and it's within the holy dragon's basin, so it's heavily guarded.
Pang: The hall is surrounded by three walls, actually, one per sect.
Pang: Unfortunately, we'll have to get through security if we want to use the front door. Otherwise, we'll have to scale the walls...
Elio: But... Pang, there's no way you can get through security.
Pang: I know, which Is why I'll need the qilin lord's help. I have to get in there and help my friends!
Tindoiimu: (Hmm... So the Tiger Tribe has at least one member who understands friendship...)
Juan-Yun: I know I'm the qilin lord, but I still don't think I could get the guards to look the other way...
Pang: But then—
Juan-Yun: Don't worry~ I've got a plan that might get all of us inside.
Tindoiimu: Why do I need to be a part of this?
Juan-Yun: Because, you're the only one here who has any right to be with me.
Juan-Yun: Plus, I thought you wanted to help. That's why you're here, isn't it?

Tindoiimu: ...Alright, alright...
Well, let's go if we're gonna go.
Juan-Yun: Thank you, princess.
Wolf Warrior: Stop right there! No one is allowed on Alliance Hall grounds without—
Tindoiimu: My talisman is right here. Or do you want to lock out one of your tournament's contestants?
Wolf Warrior: Eh? It's the insect princess?
Tindoiimu: Let me pass.
Juan-Yun: Princess! Slow down! Please, let me catch up.
Wolf Warrior: Qilin Lord? What happened?
Juan-Yun: Nothing, I just... need to talk to the princess about something.
Wolf Warrior: (So are those rumors true? He's got the hots for her?)
Juan-Yun: ...You know what, I should probably give her a gift, first.
Juan-Yun: Arbiter Maeok gave me some beautiful purple jade, but I left it in storage within the hall.
Juan-Yun: Could I trouble you two strapping young lads to bring it up to the princess' quarters for me?
Wolf Warrior: Uhh... I don't think we should leave our posts.
Juan-Yun: Ah, too bad. Maeok gave me two small jade necklaces, too. I was going to give them to you both for your trouble, but if you don't have time...
Wolf Warrior: Whoa, whoa, it's just moving a piece of jade, how long could it take? Let's help the man!
Elio: I see the Alliance Hall is a paragon of integrity...
Pang: Despicable...
Tica: Hey, at least it worked! Quick, while we have the chance!

Tiger Warrior: Those two left their posts again...
Hmph! Us tigers are so much more reliable than those wolves...
Pang: Agh! Turn back!
Tiger Warrior: You... Aren't you that fugitive!? Someone, help! They're trying to break into the Alliance Hall!
Tiger Warrior: Close the gates! Call General Shun!
Tica: Crap, they're calling for backup!
Elio: Pang, leave this to us. Can you get over the walls?
Pang: But... you...
Elio: Your friend needs us more than we do. Don't worry, Tica and I can handle these goons.
Pang: Thank you. I'll meet up with you later.
Elio: Sorry folks, I'm gonna have to ask you to wait here.
Tiger Warrior: Damn human!
Tica: Heyy~ Who knew Elio had such a wily side to him!
Elio: Heh...
Tica: It's okay, I've been waiting for this moment, too. It's my responsibility as team leader!
Tica: Comrade Pang, you better give 'em your best!
